      "content": "The key takeaway for USMLE is the primary white blood cell response. Neutrophilia, an increase in neutrophils, is classically associated with acute bacterial infections. Conversely, lymphocytosis, an increase in lymphocytes, is often seen in viral infections or chronic conditions. Remember this simple pairing: bacteria $\\rightarrow$ neutrophils (acute), and viruses $\\rightarrow$ lymphocytes (chronic/subacute).",
